# ASCII_Art

**Short description:**  
Image editing tool converting raster images into ASCII-art representations :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}

## Features
- üîß OOP-driven conversion pipeline (CharConverter, MyChar, SubImgCharMatcher, SubImagesHolder, AsciiArtAlgorithm)  
- ‚öôÔ∏è Supports customizable character-sets & rounding methods  
- üéØ Outputs to console or HTML (HtmlAsciiOutput / ConsoleAsciiOutput)

## Demo / Screenshot
Open one of the HTML outputs in `ascii_output/` to see rendered ASCII art.

## Getting Started
```bash
git clone https://github.com/ronlevin1/ASCII_Art.git
cd ASCII_Art
# compile all .java under ascii_art/
javac -d out $(find ascii_art -name "*.java")
````

## Usage

Run the interactive shell to convert an image:

```bash
java -cp out ascii_art.Shell
# then enter commands, for example:
# load path/to/image.png
# resolution 100x50
# output html out.html
# convert
```

## Structure

```
ascii_art/              # core conversion classes & Shell UI  
image/                  # sample input images  
examples/               # example commands & scripts  
ascii_output/           # saved ASCII-art outputs (HTML & text)  
image_char_matching/    # char-brightness matching utilities  
tests/                  # JUnit test suite  
```

## Technologies

* Language: Java
* Testing: JUnit
* Build: plain `javac` / `java` (no external dependencies)

